verbose_text: Higher levels of alpha-carotene and beta-carotene were associated with decreased risk of early and late AMD in some studies,194, 201, 202 but most studies did not find any association.189, 192, 194, 195 Two studies reported even an increased risk of developing late AMD in those consuming higher levels of dietary beta-carotene.196, 203 Thus, the protective effect of beta-carotene (and alpha-carotene) levels in AMD progression is not conclusive.
